docs.snippet: WASHINGTON, Oct. 22--Bolivia's President, Victor Paz Estenssoro, who led a social revolution in his country 11 years ago, was hailed today by Presdent Kennedy as a pioneer of the Alliance for Progress.

docs.snippet: POLITICALLY speaking, there is only one jefe, or  chief, in Bolivia. His name is Victor Paz Estenssoro. Mr. Paz, who is 56 years old, is completing his second fouryear term as President. Elections will be held next May.
